Supplementary to any existing authority granted by law, counties and municipal corporations shall be authorized to expend public funds and participate in community development block grant programs and other federal programs to construct facilities to carry out the following purposes:
(A)  Providing day-care services primarily to the children of persons of low and moderate income;

(B)  Providing services to elderly persons;

(C)  Providing health education, literacy and English language instruction, mental health and disability services, legal assistance, emergency food, and medical assistance to low and moderate income persons; and(D)  Any combination of services authorized in this paragraph.

